Vendored MMQ/MMVQ device kernels from llama.cpp
===============================================

Source: https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
Pinned upstream commit: 5fd2dc2c41c342a75c26f9756ca6b1814ed05fb4
License: MIT (see below)

Vendored file(s):
  mmq.cuh   - copied verbatim from ggml/src/ggml-cuda/mmq.cuh with ONE surgical
              edit (marked "VENDOR EDIT (gemm/main)"): the two device kernels
              `mul_mat_q` and `mul_mat_q_stream_k_fixup` were changed from
              `static __global__` to `static __device__` so that stable-named
              extern "C" trampolines in ../mmq_kernels.cu can call them (a
              __global__ cannot be launched from another __global__). The
              `__launch_bounds__` qualifiers (illegal on a __device__ function)
              were moved to the trampolines.

  mmvq.cuh  - device-only extract of ggml/src/ggml-cuda/mmvq.cu (the decode
              matvec), marked "VENDOR EDIT (gemm/main)": kept the helpers
              (mmvq_parameter_table_id, get_vec_dot_q_cuda, get_vdr_mmvq,
              get_device_table_id, calc_nwarps/calc_rows_per_block) and the
              `mul_mat_vec_q` template, changed `static __global__` ->
              `static __device__` with __launch_bounds__ moved to the
              ../mmvq_kernels.cu trampolines; dropped the MoE kernel + host
              launch code. ADDED by-value reimplementations of
              vec_dot_iq3_s/iq2_s (`mmvq_vd_*_byval`) routed via mmvq_vecdot<>:
              nvcc 13.2/sm_120a miscompiles the upstream const-int&-param
              versions when inlined into mul_mat_vec_q (the others are unchanged).

The remaining headers (common.cuh, mma.cuh, vecdotq.cuh, ggml-common.h,
ggml.h, ...) are NOT copied; mmq_kernels.cu / mmvq_kernels.cu include them
directly from the upstream tree via -I. The activation quantizers
(`quantize_mmq_q8_1` for MMQ, regular `block_q8_1` for MMVQ) are copied
verbatim into the respective *_kernels.cu (also MIT, same commit).

